cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.NE 

This paper deals with deep learning techniques for remote photoplethysmography, which involves analyzing color signals from facial regions to estimate heart rate values. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also discusses the use of combined loss functions, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) research. Finally, the paper addresses the problem of heart rate estimation, which is a topic in neuroscience (cs.NE).
